## STACK (this project)
- Language: TypeScript (strict mode, noUncheckedIndexedAccess, exactOptionalPropertyTypes)
- Frontend: Astro 4.16 — `web/` directory, Node SSR via `@astrojs/node` standalone
- Backend: Hono 4
- Runtime: Bun
- Database: libsql / bun:sqlite + Drizzle ORM (driver auto-selected: `file:` → bun:sqlite, `libsql:`/`https:` → @libsql/client)
- Auth: Clerk — API-only JWT verify via `@clerk/backend`. Never roll your own.
- Email: Resend — optional until email send routes exist (`RESEND_API_KEY`)
- Payments: not used
- Deploy: Fly.io (planned — see TODOS.md)

## SOURCE OF TRUTH
Stack decisions live in `CLAUDE.md`. This file is a Cursor-facing summary.
If they conflict, `CLAUDE.md` wins.

## PATTERNS (always apply)
- Functional patterns preferred over classes where it makes sense
- Typed errors — never swallow silently, always log or propagate
- Named exports over default exports
- Barrel files (index.ts) only when module surface is stable
- REST APIs: consistent error response shape across all endpoints
- Validate inputs at route handler level before business logic
- Parameterized queries always — never string interpolation in SQL
- Migrations: always reversible, never destructive without backup step
- Webhook handlers: verify signature, return 200 before processing
- Docker: no root in containers, multi-stage builds, .dockerignore required
- Env vars via .env or secrets manager — never hardcoded
- Idempotent scripts — running twice must not break anything
